The paper discusses the impact of uncle blocks on the profitability of selfish mining in Ethereum, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also analyzes the impact of network delays on the expected revenue for miners, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of Monte Carlo simulation to quantify the effect of uncle blocks on profitability and security is related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
